{"questionId":"9067425","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Propene is an important starting material for many products. The following shows some compounds which can be made from propene, C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>6</sub>.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><br>Propene (C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>6</sub>) → C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>7</sub>Cl → C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>8</sub>O → C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>6</sub>O</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Consider the conversion of propene to C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>7</sub>Cl.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">State the IUPAC name of the major product.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">2-chloropropane ✔</span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9067425","referenceCode":"19N.2.hl.TZ0.3a(ii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"State the IUPAC name of the major product.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a(ii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry","10.1 Fundamentals of organic chemistry","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}